om\": 757, \"to\": 770}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The race marked the first time in the Olympics that Delgaco posted a sub-7:50 mark after recording 7:56.26 in theheats, 7:55.00 in therepechage, 7:58.30 in thequarterfinals, and 8:00.18 in theclassification semifinal C/D.\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 994, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The race\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 781}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 803}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 819}, {\"ngram\": \"Delgaco\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 832}, {\"ngram\": \"a sub-7:50 mark\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 855}, {\"ngram\": \"7:56.26\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 879}, {\"ngram\": \"theheats\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 891}, {\"ngram\": \"therepechage\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 916}, {\"ngram\": \"thequarterfinals\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 945}, {\"ngram\": \"theclassification semifinal C/D.\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 994}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is also faster than her time of 7:49.39, set during the World Rowing Asian and Oceanian Qualification Regatta in April where she became thePhilippines' first female rower to qualify for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1198, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her time\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1027}, {\"ngram\": \"7:49.39\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1038}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Rowing Asian and Oceanian Qualification Regatta\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1108}, {\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1117}, {\"ngram\": \"thePhilippines' first female rower\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1169}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1197}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paraguay's Alejandra Alonso Alderete topped the classification race with 7:42.09 for 19th place, while Iran's Fatemeh Mojallal (7:46.08) and Turkey's Elis Ozbay (7:46.95) finished behind Delgaco for 21st and 22nd places, respectively.\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1200, \"end\": 1208, \"title\": \"http://db